results.title: The Case of The Mysterious Purse
results.description:
The Case of the Mysterious Purse

It was a fog and cheery night.  I just left an all-day Tupperware party...and...as I happily carried my 16oz. mug of almond chocolate milk…walking towards home, I saw an unattended purse sitting on a metal bench at the bus stop.

It quickly caught my eye because I noticed it appeared to be an expensive looking, designer made handbag…with its shiny, gold labels securely attached to a thick, fine leather cover.  To me, it surely looked like a prize winning find.

What made it more tempting to snatch was the single, solar lightbulb spot lighting it as it sat there glistening all by its lonesome.

My curiosity almost got the best of me after several questions popped into my head. 

For example:

1.  Should I judge a purse by its cover?  If I dare grab it and run…will its contents be a good steal?

2.  Why was it left there?  A forgetful woman who was too much in a hurry to catch a ride home?

3.  That its beauty was in actuality a piece of bait for an unsuspecting thief…luring them to nibble and bite…resulting in spending the night behind bars?

4.  While observing from a distance…slowly sipping my daily addiction, I started to pick my knows and remember what I learned as a child – that taking someone’s belongings is not right…and...I always wanted to write.

 5.  So…there sat an unattended, expensive looking designer labeled purse.  In these days and times, it’s easily interpreted as a suspicious looking package…that might give more than a bang for its buck… resulting in many pieces to this puzzle.

6.  Would it be worth the risk of possibly being whisked away by the law?

7.  Hmm…I could flip a coin and let chance be my destiny…no?

8.  Making decisions can be difficult…especially if one thinks that looks are deceiving sometimes.

Oh…what to do….what to Doo!  This is too much doo-doo to think about.

As I walked away, my curiosity eventually vanished.  If I let curiosity out of the bag…would it kill the cat?

Moral of the Story:  Pick your knows before you judge a bag by its cover – quick decisions can result in getting a bang for your buck or banging to the tune of righting word puzzles.  :)

em

p.s.  the items displayed in the picture are not for sale in this listing...just the case of the mysterious purse story.  Thx.

Support Operation Smile
